## Introduction
Toggles are simple on/off switches for features like flying, particle effects, or custom powers.

### Example: Toggle Player Flight
```java
Map<UUID, Boolean> flyingPlayers = new HashMap<>();

public void toggleFlight(Player player) {
    boolean currentlyFlying = flyingPlayers.getOrDefault(player.getUniqueId(), false);
    player.setAllowFlight(!currentlyFlying);
    player.setFlying(!currentlyFlying);
    flyingPlayers.put(player.getUniqueId(), !currentlyFlying);
    player.sendMessage("Flight is now " + (!currentlyFlying ? "enabled" : "disabled"));
}
```

### Logic Explanation
- Store toggle state in a Map using player UUID.
- Flip state each time method is called.
- Provide feedback to the player with a message.

### Edge Cases & Warnings
- Always check permissions if needed.
- Ensure toggles persist if necessary (e.g., saved in config for reload).
- Avoid storing too many temporary maps without cleanup.

## Introduction
Toggles are also useful for custom powers, particle effects, or abilities.

### Example: Toggle Particle Trail
```java
Map<UUID, Boolean> trailToggles = new HashMap<>();

public void toggleTrail(Player player) {
    boolean hasTrail = trailToggles.getOrDefault(player.getUniqueId(), false);
    trailToggles.put(player.getUniqueId(), !hasTrail);
    player.sendMessage("Particle trail " + (!hasTrail ? "enabled" : "disabled"));
}
```

### Logic Explanation
- Same principle as flight toggle.
- Can be used for any on/off plugin feature.
- Check toggle state in events (e.g., `PlayerMoveEvent` to spawn particles).

### Edge Cases & Warnings
- Remember to remove players from toggle map if they leave the server to avoid memory leaks.
- Consider using persistent storage if toggle should survive restarts.

## Introduction
Some toggles should remain active even after the player leaves or the server restarts.

### Example: Save Toggles in Config
```java
// On toggle change
config.set("players." + player.getUniqueId() + ".flight", !currentlyFlying);
saveConfig();

// On player join
boolean enabled = config.getBoolean("players." + player.getUniqueId() + ".flight", false);
player.setAllowFlight(enabled);
player.setFlying(enabled);
```

### Logic Explanation
- Store toggle state in config.yml or database.
- Load toggle state when player joins.
- Ensures features persist across sessions.

### Edge Cases & Warnings
- Config writes on every toggle may cause IO overhead; consider batching.
- Default values prevent null errors.
- Always validate data read from config.
